{{Short description|Maldivian mathematician}} {{Infobox scientist | name = Hassan Ugail | native_name = | native_name_lang = Dhivehi | birth_place = [[Hithadhoo (Seenu Atoll)|Hithadhoo, Addu City]], [[Maldive Islands|Maldives]] | birth_date = 24 September | nationality = Maldivian | fields = [[Visual Computing]] | thesis_title = Design, analysis and optimisation in an interactive environment | thesis_url = https://leeds.primo.exlibrisgroup.com/discovery/fulldisplay?vid=44LEE_INST:VU1&docid=alma991006070719705181 | thesis_year = 2000 | alma_mater = {{Plainlist| * [[King's College London]] (BSc 1995, PGCE 1996) * [[University of Leeds]] (PhD 2000)}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Hassan Ugail, Professor of Visual Computing, Faculty of Engineering & Informatics / Media Design and Technology - Staff Profiles| url=https://www.brad.ac.uk/staff/hugail|access-date=2019-08-12}}</ref> | workplaces = {{Plainlist| * [[University of Leeds]] Research Fellow (20002002) * [[University of Bradford]] (2002present)}} | image = | image_size = | spouse = Livshana Shareef | caption = }} Professor '''Hassan Ugail''' is a mathematician and a computer scientist. He is currently working as a Professor of Visual Computing at the School of Engineering and Informatics at the [[University of Bradford]].<ref name="ubradfordstaffprofile">{{cite web |url=https://www.brad.ac.uk/ei/media-design-technology/staff-profiles/profile/?u=hugail|title=University of Bradford: School of Engineering and Informatics (Staff Contacts)|access-date=2019-08-12}}</ref> Professor Ugail is the first [[Maldivians|Maldivian]] to obtain a PhD in mathematics. He is also the first and to date the only [[Republic of the Maldives|Maldivian]] to receive a [[professorship]] in the field of Science.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.haveeru.com.mv/feature/53370|url-status=dead|title=Ugail's vision of breeding Maldivian scientists|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303231903/http://www.haveeru.com.mv/feature/53370|archive-date=2016-03